<br>
<br>
The Halfling was eating his bread and cheese rather quickly, his eyes looking to the sides of him, nervously. The bartender, Crow, was polishing his wood counter, talking to a bardmaid about the local guards. An Erudite was talking to a Half Elf maiden, his voice too low to be identified. A man walked in, cloaked in scarlet. A large sword was strapped to his side. He sat down at a lone table off in the corner. The barmaid walked up to the man to ask if he wanted the daily special but he just asked to be left alone. The man took out a silver puch and emptied its contents. The whole tavern seemed to be watching him. A few coins fell out and clinked onto the wooden surface of the table. 'Mighty fine prize ye got there, friend. With those coins, you might be able to sleep under a good roof tonight with a good supper in yer belly.' Crow eyed the coins very carefully, intrigued by them, for he had never seen such designs. The man fingered around in the pouch and pulled out a peice of paper. He did not open it but continued to stare at it for a bit. The Erudite walked up to the cloaked man and sat down next to him. 'Hail, my name is Udare, Enchanter from the great land of Odus. Can I buy you a drink?' The man said nothing, still looking at the paper. 'Are you ok, friend?' The man took his gaze off the papers, looked at the Erudite, and smiled. He placed the paper in the Erudites hand. 'Now you shall see the true might of Bertoxxolous!' The cloaked man then screamed, grabbed his heart, and dropped to the ground. The Erudite opened the paper and he was taken aback at what he read. 'TO THE CITIZENS OF NORRATH, AT DAWN, HELL SHALL BE UNLEASHED ON THOSE WHO ARE HOLY AND TRUE!! MANY WILL PERISH IN THE NAME OF BERTOXXOLOUS!!'<br>
The Erudite dropped the piece of paper and ran out of the bar, heading to the Temple of Life...<br>
