<br>
'If Bertoxxolous is coming, we need to stand together and fight him. He is one and we are many! He shall fall to the forces of good!' Derkis looked at the many people before him. 'I shall not die before I know that Bertoxxolous does not destroy another land!' All of a sudden, the ground shakes lightly. The group looks around to see what caused the rumble. The sky begins to darken and turn red, the air begins to reak of rottening flesh, and many men and women are running around, trying to find a safe hiding place. 'Here he comes!' 'Save yourselves!' 'Prepare for battle!' Many of them scream. A dark shadow is seen in the sky, it begins to descend. After a few minutes, the beast lands and starts rampaging towards the tunnel. A few groups of guards try to stop the beast but are quickly and brutally killed. Many are killed before the beast gets to the tunnel. 'I am Bertoxxolous' inhuman form. My Children! Come join my side!' A few Necromancers, Warriors, and Shadowknights walk over to the beast. 'Good, let the fight begin!!!' The beasts attacks an Elf standing in the middle of the group. It takes its tucks and launches the poor elf in the air. The elf soars into the heavens and is soon out of sight. A shaman tries to disease the beast, but it bounces of the beast and kills the shaman. A Warrior of Bertoxxolous brandishes his swords, turns to the beast, and impales it. The Beast looks down at the warrior, roars, and falls down, smashing the warrior in hope of killing him. Blood begins to cover the soft ground and stains everything red. The warrior, almost dead, looks up at his friend and says,' I told you I wouldn't let Bertoxxolous destroy this land...' Saying that, Derkis's eyes rolled back into his head and fell into a peaceful eternal slumber.<br>
